<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('components/head'); -%>

<body>
  <%- include('components/header'); -%>
  <main class="about-page">
    <section class="intro-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>About Our Inventory Management App</h1>
        <p>Welcome to our Inventory Management App, your one-stop solution for efficient inventory control and management. Our app is designed to help you easily track and manage your inventory, ensuring that you always have the right products at the right time.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="features-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Categories:</strong> Organize your products into categories for better management.</li>
          <li><strong>Items:</strong> Add, edit, and delete items with ease, including details such as name, description, stock, price, and category.</li>
          <li><strong>Search and Filter:</strong> Quickly find items or categories using the search and filter functionality.</li>
          <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Use our app on any device, whether it's a desktop, tablet, or smartphone.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="how-it-works-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Create Categories:</strong> Start by creating categories to organize your products.</li>
          <li><strong>Add Items:</strong> Once categories are set, add items to your inventory with relevant details.</li>
          <li><strong>Manage Inventory:</strong> Use the app to edit or delete items and categories as needed.</li>
          <li><strong>Track Stock:</strong> Keep an eye on stock levels and update quantities as items are added or removed.</li>
          <li><strong>Search and Filter:</strong> Utilize the search bar and filters to quickly locate specific items or categories.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <%- include('components/footer'); -%>
</body>

</html>